23/03/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The trial stemming from last year's bombing of a police station in Bugojno started on Tuesday (March 22nd) with opening statements by prosecutors. They say defendants Haris Causevic, Adnan Haracic and Naser Palislamovic committed the crime with the help of Emin Osmanagic, Haris Spago and Nedzad Kesko. One police officer was killed and several others were injured in the June attack. Prosecutor Ozrenka Neskovic told the court that the group wanted to intimidate the public and destabilise the country. (RTRS, Srna, Dnevni Avaz, Tanjug - 22/03/11)
